# Installation

1. Put TexXpander.sh somewhere on your system. I've chosen ~/Softwares folder.
2. Create a keyboard shortcut that calls ~/Softwares/TexXpander.sh
3. Create a ~/Softwares/TexXpander directory where you store text files for expanding abbreviations

TexXpander relies on a couple command line tools:

- xdotool
- zenity
- xsel

